T209 and were distributed in packs of Contentnea Cigarettes (Wilson, NC) in 1909-1910. The cards appeared in two versions: Series One (First Series) displayed color lithographs of players that resembled the popular T206 format, and Series Two (Photo Series) reproduced black-and-white photographs of players in field or studio poses.
